{
  "texts": [
    "To deal with overfitting, two hyperparameters were optimized; the minimal number of data in one leaf and the maximum depth of the tree model.",
    "LR calculates the likelihood of an event occurring based on an independent variable dataset [32].",
    "The magnitude of the LR coefficients represents the relative importance of each independent variable in influencing the prediction.",
    "Larger coefficient values indicate a stronger impact on the prediction, while smaller coefficients suggest a weaker influence.",
    "This interpretation allows for identifying the importance of each independent variable in the prediction."
  ]
}